51–1206":"1151–1206","1152–1173":"1152–1173","1153–Male":"1153–Deceased","1155–Male":"1155–Deceased","1157–Male":"1157–Deceased","1159–Male":"1159–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1172–Female":"1172–Deceased","1128–1219":"1128–1219","1127–1162":"1127–from8January1162to7January1163","1153":"1153","1152":"1152","1162":"from 8 January 1162 to 7 January 1163","1173":"1173","1151":"1151","1172":"1172","ABT 1150":"about 1150","1206":"1206","Abt 1152":"about 1152","1128":"1128","1127":"1127","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1146":"1146","1155":"1155","after 1173":"after 1173","1219":"1219","Ellenhall, Stafford, England":"Ellenhall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Noel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Pierre, Normand, Antoine, Jacques, Alphonse, Leonce, Lucien, Marcel, Damien, Emile, Francois.","French and Walloon (<b>Noël</b>); English: from the Old French personal name <i>Noël</i>, Middle English <i>Noel</i>, from Old French <i>no(u)el</i> ‘Christmas’ (from Latin <i>natalis (dies)</i> ‘birthday’), used for someone born during the Christmas period. Alternatively, a nickname for someone who had some special connection with the Christmas season, such as owing the particular feudal duty of providing a yule-log to the lord of the manor, or having given a memorable performance as the Lord of Misrule. This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium. Compare   Christmas   and   Newell  .","English: sometimes a post-medieval variant of <b>Knowle</b> and   Knoll   (see   Knowles  ). The loss of /k/ before /n/ is known in everyday speech by the 17th century and may have been earlier."],"variants":[{"name":"Nowell","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): variant of   Noel  ,   Knowles  , or   Newell  ."]},{"name":"Christmas","meanings":["English (southeastern): nickname from Middle English <i>Criste(s)masse</i>, <i>-messe</i> ‘Christmas Day’, also ‘the Christmas season’, perhaps for someone who was born at Christmas or one who played the part of the King of Christmas in Yuletide games. The name was also established in County Waterford, Ireland, in 1622.","Americanized form (translation into English) of French <b>Noël</b> (see   Noel  )."]},{"name":"Nadal","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Miguel, Francisco, Jose, Luis, Caridad, Digna, Jaime, Juan, Juan Carlos, Manuel, Otilio.","Catalan and French (Occitan): from the personal name <i>Nadal</i>, from <i>nadal</i> ‘Christmas’ (from Latin <i>natalis</i> ‘birthday’), the name given to a child born on that day or during that time of year. Compare   Noel  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice de Noel was born about 1152, in Ellenhall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Robert Noell, was 26 and her mother, Lady Alice de Montfort, was 27. She died after 1173."},"et":{"Abt 1152–after 1173":"umbes 1152–pärast 1173","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","1151–1206":"1151–1206","1152–1173":"1152–1173","1153–Male":"1153–Surnud","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1157–Male":"1157–Surnud","1159–Male":"1159–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1172–Female":"1172–Surnud","1128–1219":"1128–1219","1127–1162":"1127–8.jaanuar1162kuni7.jaanuar1163","1153":"1153","1152":"1152","1162":"8. jaanuar 1162 kuni 7. jaanuar 1163","1173":"1173","1151":"1151","1172":"1172","ABT 1150":"umbes 1150","1206":"1206","Abt 1152":"umbes 1152","1128":"1128","1127":"1127","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1146":"1146","1155":"1155","after 1173":"pärast 1173","1219":"1219","Ellenhall, Stafford, England":"Ellenhall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1152–after 1173":"noin 1152–1173 jälkeen","1146–Male":"1146–Kuollut","1151–1206":"1151–1206","1152–1173":"1152–1173","1153–Male":"1153–Kuollut","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1157–Male":"1157–Kuollut","1159–Male":"1159–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1172–Female":"1172–Kuollut","1128–1219":"1128–1219","1127–1162":"1127–vuodesta8.tammikuuta1162vuoteen7.tammikuuta1163","1153":"1153","1152":"1152","1162":"vuodesta 8. tammikuuta 1162 vuoteen 7. tammikuuta 1163","1173":"1173","1151":"1151","1172":"1172","ABT 1150":"noin 1150","1206":"1206","Abt 1152":"noin 1152","1128":"1128","1127":"1127","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1146":"1146","1155":"1155","after 1173":"1173 jälkeen","1219":"1219","Ellenhal